ğŸ”¹ How Python Stores These Variables

Integers (int) like player_health = 100 are immutableâ€”when we modify them, Python creates a new object in memory.
Lists (list) like player_inventory are mutableâ€”changes directly modify the memory location.
ğŸ’¡ Testing Pythonâ€™s Memory Model

python
Copy
Edit
x = 100
y = x
print(id(x), id(y))  # Same memory address!

x += 10
print(id(x), id(y))  # Now different! (x was reassigned)
ğŸ” Lesson: Numbers are immutable, while lists are mutable!

