âš”ï¸ Chapter 12: Implementing an Enemy AI
"A warrior is only as strong as their greatest enemy."

Right now, combat is staticâ€”enemies do not react intelligently.
Let's change that by giving our enemies decision-making abilities.

ğŸ§  Step 1: Creating an Enemy Class
python
Copy
Edit
import random

class Enemy:
    def __init__(self, name, health, attack_power):
        self.name = name
        self.health = health
        self.attack_power = attack_power

    def attack(self):
        return random.randint(5, self.attack_power)

    def take_damage(self, damage):
        self.health -= damage
        print(f"{self.name} takes {damage} damage! Health: {self.health}")

# Create an enemy instance
goblin = Enemy("Goblin", 50, 15)
ğŸ¤– Step 2: AI-Based Enemy Attacks
Instead of always attacking, enemies will have different strategies.

python
Copy
Edit
def enemy_turn(enemy, player_health):
    action = random.choice(["attack", "defend", "taunt"])

    if action == "attack":
        damage = enemy.attack()
        print(f"{enemy.name} attacks! You take {damage} damage.")
        return player_health - damage
    elif action == "defend":
        print(f"{enemy.name} raises its defenses!")
    else:
        print(f"{enemy.name} taunts you!")
    
    return player_health
ğŸ› ï¸ Step 3: Adding Enemy AI to Combat
python
Copy
Edit
player_health = 100
goblin = Enemy("Goblin", 50, 15)

while player_health > 0 and goblin.health > 0:
    action = input("Attack or Run: ").lower()

    if action == "attack":
        damage = random.randint(10, 20)
        goblin.take_damage(damage)

        if goblin.health <= 0:
            print("You defeated the Goblin!")
            break

        player_health = enemy_turn(goblin, player_health)

    elif action == "run":
        print("You fled the battle!")
        break

if player_health <= 0:
    print("You have been defeated!")
âœ… Challenge: Introduce more enemy types with unique attack styles.

ğŸ’¾ Chapter 13: Saving & Loading Game Progress
"A heroâ€™s tale must be recorded, lest it be forgotten."

ğŸ“Œ The Problem
