ğŸ¨ Chapter 14: Making the Game Graphical with Pygame
"A true Grandmaster does not only code, but brings worlds to life."

ğŸ“Œ The Problem
Right now, our game is text-based.

ğŸ“Œ The Solution
We will use Pygame to create a 2D graphical RPG.

ğŸ–¥ï¸ Step 1: Setting Up Pygame
python
Copy
Edit
import pygame

pygame.init()
screen = pygame.display.set_mode((800, 600))
pygame.display.set_caption("Grandmasterâ€™s Quest")

running = True
while running:
    for event in pygame.event.get():
        if event.type == pygame.QUIT:
            running = False

pygame.quit()
ğŸƒ Step 2: Moving the Character
python
Copy
Edit
player_x, player_y = 400, 300
speed = 5

while running:
    keys = pygame.key.get_pressed()

    if keys[pygame.K_LEFT]: player_x -= speed
    if keys[pygame.K_RIGHT]: player_x += speed
    if keys[pygame.K_UP]: player_y -= speed
    if keys[pygame.K_DOWN]: player_y += speed

    screen.fill((0, 0, 0))  # Clear screen
    pygame.draw.rect(screen, (0, 255, 0), (player_x, player_y, 40, 40))  # Player character
    pygame.display.update()
âœ… Challenge: Implement a map for the player to navigate.

